Description: Per-fan PID control for Linux desktop systems
 KDE Fan Control provides flexible, per-fan PID control for Linux desktop
 machines where the standard fancontrol utility is too rigid or cumbersome.
 It runs a privileged daemon that manages fan speeds using selectable
 temperature inputs or aggregated sensor groups, and exposes control
 through DBus to a KDE/Qt6 GUI, system tray app, and CLI.
 .
 Features include:
  - Per-fan PID control with configurable gains, limits, and sample intervals
  - Automatic hardware discovery via Linux hwmon sysfs interface
  - KDE-native GUI with overview, inventory, and fan detail pages
  - System tray integration with status notifications
  - Staged draft/applied configuration lifecycle with validation
  - Auto-tune wizard for suggesting PID gains
  - Polkit-authenticated privileged operations
  - Fail-safe fallback: fans driven to maximum speed on daemon failure